### Links/relationships

This dataset uses a value of 2.2802997e-09 kg/m2/s to represent 10GtC/year. This value is copied from the flat10 emissions ancillary (/g/data/vk83/configurations/inputs/access-esm1p6/modern/flat10/atmosphere/forcing/global.N96/2025.12.05/CO2_fluxes_flat10.anc) and rounded to 7 decimals.


### Recommended citation

https://doi.org/10.5194/gmd-17-8141-2024

## Data and Files

### File List

```
CO2_fluxes_flat10CDR.anc                    CO2 emissions ancillary file
```

### Data Specific Information

CO2_fluxes_flat10CDR.anc contains gridded time varying CO2 fluxes to the atmosphere in kg(CO2)/m2/s, for use in the CMIP7 esm-flat10-cdr experiment. Emissions evolve following the specification in https://doi.org/10.5194/gmd-17-8141-2024 (Table 1). Total emissions initially decline linearly from 10GtC/year to -10GtC/year over 100 years, remain flat at -10GtC/year for 100 years, and swap to 0 emissions for the remaining years. A 200 year period of zero emissions has been chosen here. During the interpolation, emissions values change between years but remain constant within each year.

This dataset starts at year 301 to match the starting year in the restart file (/g/data/vk83/configurations/inputs/access-esm1p6/modern/flat10-zec/restart/2026.05.27) selected for the esm-flat10-cdr experiment.

## Methodological information

This file was generated with commit f745597 of https://github.com/ACCESS-NRI/CMIP7-Input/pull/130, using the arguments "--year-start 301 --nyear-zero 200".